review_blob: Pours out a hazy golden apperance with a really nice fluffy white head..slight hoppy bitterness with a nice fruity aroma..has a nice soft mouthfull..this is a wonderfull well balanced trappist beer...enjoy
Amber in color with a thin head....tasted almost soapy at first with a strange aftertaste...not a big fan but mabe my taste was off lol
Watered down urine in a bottle...is this even beer??? Honestly my father drinks this cause he cant handle a flavorfull beer lol
Carbonated Urine in a bottle...Im not really sure why this beer ever became popular
Draft..Pour is a dark thick with a wonderful cream colored head...dark chocolate/java bean notes...the Standard bar none... enjoy

Bottle..A nice amber haze when poured with little to no head and no lacing...a sweet grapefruit in aroma. though as it warms a definate alcohol notes do appear.. I was surprised in the smoothness in this beer..it had a nice crisp finish..enjoy

Bottle..Batch 8907... I love the aroma of this beer..the apricot/grapefruit aroma was so intense yet pleasurable that i sat and smelled this beer for a good 5 min just enjoying the armoma...the sweet intense flavor with the power of the hops were a real treat..buy this beer..enjoy

Bottle..Bought two bottles of this for a friend home from basic training and we were both blown away..nice spicy hoppy flavor to compliment this amber colored beer..i will buy this every year during the holidays....enjoy
Bottle...First time ive tried a Christmas beer and was pleased with what i got....very hazy pour..could definatly taste cinnamon and some spice in this beer and ejoyed it alot...enjoy
Bottle..Have i mentioned that Samuel Smiths make beer that I enjoy lol... Nice nutty brown apperance with very nice lacing...enjoyable clean sweet finish.. definate nutty notes...Enjoy
A spicy rasin feel to this amber brown colored beer.. taste is complex in nature and has a nice crisp finish.. Enjoy
Very nice Porter...Very dark and intense flavor...another winner from the fine brewery..Enjoy

The first time i tried this was on tap on the recomendation of my Brother in Law and ive never looked back lol...This beer is amazing.. with its very dark coloration and tan head..a slight dark chocolate taste but hoppy at the finish..be careful though at 10.5 abv these will catch up with you quickly...enjoy
This is truely a great Stout...Samuel Smiths make great beers and this is one of my favorites..Nice aroma with and very creamy..I recomend this beer year round
